President Biden delivered a speech at the Carpenters Pittsburgh Training Center in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, outlining his vision for rebuilding the backbone of America. He emphasized the importance of investing in infrastructure, including transportation, broadband, and clean energy, as well as addressing climate change and creating jobs. Biden proposed a plan that includes modernizing transportation infrastructure, building new rail corridors and transit lines, and upgrading affordable, energy-efficient housing. He also highlighted the need to invest in research and development, improve access to high-speed internet, and prioritize clean energy technology. To fund these investments, Biden proposed raising the corporate tax rate and implementing a global minimum tax for US corporations. He emphasized the need for bipartisan support and collaboration to achieve these goals and strengthen the United States' position in the global economy.